         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">7 Aug. [188]4 ¶ Dear Baron Mueller ¶  ¶ I am exceedingly sorry to have to trouble you again with this voucher, but Mr Walter has omitted to  ¶ fill in ¶  the receipt at the bottom of the form. ¶  If M...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.08.07a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Maiden</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MRS 7/1/349, minor outward correspondence, Powerhouse Museum, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">7 Aug. [188]4<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">editorial addition; MS is an entry in a letter-copy book. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am exceedingly sorry to have to trouble you again with this voucher, but Mr Walter has omitted to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fill in</hi>
               </seg> the receipt at the bottom of the form.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Maiden, 5 August 1884 (in this edition as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>84-08-05a).</p>
               </note> If Mr Walter will only do this &amp; put it in an envelope addressed to me, you need not be troubled any further in the matter. The Auditor General is very particular in the matter of receipts.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Will you kindly let me know the cost of one of your "School Educational Collections of Plants,"<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See Lucas, Maroske &amp; Brown-May (2006), and Maroske (2007).</p>
               </note> as the Committee is desirous of exhibiting <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               </seg> in this Museum.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours truly,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. H. Maiden</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Baron Ferd. von Mueller K.C.M.G.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c</p>
         </div>
      </body>
